HOUSE BILL 1134
J1 6lr1889
By: Delegates Taveras, Lehman, and Schindler
Introduced and read first time: February 11, 2026
Assigned to: Health
A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Pharmaceutical Drugs and Devices – Gifts to Health Care Professionals –
3 Prohibition
4 FOR the purpose of prohibiting sellers of certain pharmaceutical drugs and devices from
5 giving or offering to give to health care professionals gifts in a calendar year that
6 have a total combined retail value of more than a certain amount; and generally
7 relating to gifts to health care professionals.
8 BY repealing and reenacting, without amendments,
9 Article – Health – General
10 Section 21–101(a), (f), and (g)
11 Annotated Code of Maryland
12 (2023 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
13 BY adding to
14 Article – Health – General
15 Section 21–1114 and 21–1207
16 Annotated Code of Maryland
17 (2023 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
18 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
19 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
20 Article – Health – General
21 21–101.
22 (a) In this title the following words have the meanings indicated.
23 (f) “Device” means any instrument, apparatus, or contrivance, or any part or
24 accessory of an instrument, apparatus, or contrivance, that is intended:
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
[Brackets] indicate matter deleted from exist in g l aw . *hb1134*

2 HOUSE BILL 1134
1 (1) For use in the diagnosis, cure, mitigation, treatment, or prevention of
2 human disease; or
3 (2) To affect the structure or any function of the human body for medical,
4 surgical, or therapeutic purposes.
5 (g) (1) “Drug” means any substance or component of a substance:
6 (i) That is recognized in an official compendium;
7 (ii) That is intended for use in the diagnosis, cure, mitigation,
8 treatment, or prevention of disease in human beings; or
9 (iii) Except for food, that is intended to affect the structure or any
10 function of the human body.
11 (2) “Drug” does not include a device.
12 21–1114.
13 (A) (1) IN THIS SECTION THE FOLLOWING WORDS HAVE THE MEANINGS
14 INDICATED.
15 (2) (I) “GIFT” MEANS ANY PAYMENT, FOOD, ENTERTAINMENT,
16 TRAVEL, SUBSCRIPTION, ADVANCE, SERVICE, OR ANYTHING ELSE OF VALUE
17 PROVIDED TO A HEALTH CARE PROFESSIONAL, UNLESS THE HEALTH CARE
18 PROFESSIONAL REIMBURSES THE COST AT FAIR MARKET VALUE.
19 (II) “GIFT” DOES NOT INCLUDE PEER–REVIEWED MEDICAL
20 LITERATURE.
21 (3) (I) “HEALTH CARE PROFESSIONAL” MEANS:
22 1. AN INDIVIDUAL WHO IS:
23 A. LICENSED OR CERTIFIED UNDER THE HEALTH
24 OCCUPATIONS ARTICLE; AND
25 B. AUTHORIZED TO PRESCRIBE OR RECOMMEND
26 PRESCRIBED PRODUCTS;
27 2. A PARTNERSHIP OR CORPORATION COMPOSED OF
28 THE INDIVIDUALS DESCRIBED IN ITEM 1 OF THIS SUBPARAGRAPH; OR

HOUSE BILL 1134 3
1 3. AN OFFICER, AN EMPLOYEE, AN AGENT, OR A
2 CONTRACTOR OF A PERSON DESCRIBED IN ITEM 1 OR 2 OF THIS SUBPARAGRAPH
3 WHO IS ACTING IN THE COURSE AND SCOPE OF EMPLOYMENT OR A CONTRACT
4 RELATED TO OR SUPPORTIVE OF THE PROVISION OF HEALTH CARE TO INDIVIDUALS.
5 (II) “HEALTH CARE PROFESSIONAL” DOES NOT INCLUDE AN
6 INDIVIDUAL EMPLOYED SOLELY BY A MANUFACTURER.
7 (B) A PERSON THAT SELLS DRUGS OR DEVICES MAY NOT GIVE OR OFFER TO
8 GIVE TO A HEALTH CARE PROFESSIONAL GIFTS IN A CALENDAR YEAR THAT HAVE A
9 TOTAL COMBINED RETAIL VALUE OF MORE THAN $50.
10 21–1207.
11 A PERSON WHO VIOLATES § 21–1114 OF THIS TITLE IS GUILTY OF A
12 MISDEMEANOR AND ON CONVICTION IS SUBJECT TO A FINE NOT EXCEEDING $5,000
13 OR IMPRISONMENT NOT EXCEEDING 6 MONTHS OR BOTH.
14 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
15 October 1, 2026.

